\frac{\sin\theta + \cos\theta}{\sin\theta  - \cos\theta} = \frac{5}{4}
\frac{\tan^2\theta + 1}{\tan^2\theta - 1}
\implies\frac{\tan^2\theta + 1}{\tan^2\theta - 1} = \frac{\frac{\sin^2\theta}{\cos^2\theta} + 1}{\frac{\sin^2\theta}{\cos^2\theta} - 1}
=\frac{\sin^2\theta + \cos^2\theta}{\sin^2\theta - \cos^2\theta}
=\frac{1}{\sin^2\theta - \cos^2\theta}
=\frac{1}{(\sin\theta + \cos\theta)(\sin\theta - \cos\theta)}
=\frac{\sin\theta + \cos\theta}{\sin\theta  - \cos\theta} = \frac{5}{4}
=\frac{1}{20}
\dfrac a b=\dfrac c d
a=c
b=d
\frac{\sin\theta}{\cos\theta}=\frac{5+4}{5-4}
\implies \frac{\tan^2\theta}1=\frac{9^2}1
